Imagery Description: Body: (a) Nude whiteNon Sepcifiedfleshed woman, with red drapery over right shoulder and left arm, aryballos in left hand; nude youth with phiale and fillet in upraised right hand, wreath in left, (b) draped woman seated to left on altar, with wreath and 'skewer of fruit' in right hand, large tambourines above on each side. Lid: female heads. WhiteNon Sepcifiedfleshed plastic female heads on shoulder of obverse, conical knobs on reverse.
Artist: The Painter of Naples 2585 and his circle
